        <div class="panel" id="about">
            <h1>About</h1>
            Sudoku Champs is an online platform for competitive Sudoku gameplay.
        </div>
        <div class="panel" id="rules">
            <h1>Rules</h1>
            <h2>Some games are meant to be played without rules. This is not one of them.</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>The game ends when:
                    <ol>
                        <li>The player / opponent completes the puzzle.</li>
                        <li>The player concedes the game.</li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
                <li>For head to head games, the score depends on the time taken to solve the grid, and the number of
                    unsolved cells.
                </li>
                <li>Ranking depends on:
                    <ol>
                        <li>Points: Win: 2, Loss: 0, Tie: 1.</li>
                        <li>Matches won.</li>
                        <li>Matches played.</li>
                        <li>Number of forfeits, if any.</li>
                        <li>Reputation.</li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
                <li>Practice mode results do not affect user ranking.</li>
                <li>Leaving any match midway results in an instant loss.</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
        <div class="panel" id="privacy">
            <h1>Privacy</h1>
            <p>Normally, we would rant on and on about how your privacy and rights are of utmost importance to us, and
               also a little bit on how we take several undisclosed steps towards maintaining that position. However,
               we also realize that in this day and age, our smart users have better things to do and more challenging
               Sudoku to solve, so we'll cut to the chase: We don't distribute user contact details. We never did, and
               we never will. Your contact details are only used to keep you in the game, and out of the hands of
               spammers. We hate spam as much as all of you do, possibly more. <br><br>
               Now that all the nonsense is done away with, let's move on to the <a href="/play" class="link">game</a>.
            </p>
        </div>
